				<h2><b>FAQ</b></h2>
				<p><font size="1">Frequently Asked Questions</font></p><br>

			
				<p><b><font color="white" size = 4>I added to a story, but now it's no longer listed under "Stories in Progress".  What happened?!?</font></b></h5>
				<p><font size="2">Once a story reaches 10 contributions, it is considered finished.  It is then saved in the Story Archive, which can be found by clicking the menu icon and selecting "Finished Stories".</font></p>
				<br>
				<p><b><font color="white" size = 4>Why can't I add to stories listed in the Story Archive?</font></b></p>
				<p><font size="2">StoryShare has a ten sentence limit for each story.  Once a story reaches ten sentences long, it can no longer be added to. But you can still read and enjoy it!</font></p>
				<br>
				<p><b><font color="white" size = 4>Where can I find a story I already contributed to?</font></b></p>
				<p><font size="2">All stories in progress are listed on the Collaborate page, which can be found by clicking the menu icon and selecting "Stories in Progress".</font></p>
				<br>
				<p><b><font color="white" size = 4>What if I want to edit something someone else wrote?</font></b></p>
				<p><font size="2">You can't!  That's the beauty of collaboration.</font></p>
				<br>
				<p><b><font color="white" size = 4>What if I want to edit something I already wrote?</font></b></p>
				<p><font size="2">You can't!  The purpose of StoryShare is not to "get it right", but instead to encourage writers to express whatever ideas come to mind without the pressure of perfection.</font></p>
				<p><b><font color="white" size = 4>What are the white, square icons next to the stories for?</font></b></p>
				<p><font size="2">These icons represent the number of times the story has been contributed to.  The fuller the box, the more times the story has been added to.  Once a box fills entirely (a story reaches 10 contributions), the story will be moved into the Story Archive, which can be found by clicking the menu icon and selecting "Finished Stories".  </font></p>
				
